                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <lb></lb>
                <p> <unclear reason="bad handwriting" cert="medium">Long ere </unclear> this I should have written to you concerning the dutch book 
                    
                    -  which I began translating with great energy - I was struck with the language 
                    
                    I was compelled to employ in order to render a true translation. 
                    
                    A language which would be quite unsuited to english taste. 
                    
                   In reading pats of the both in dutch &#x27; in Holland &#x27; 
                    
                    with perhaps by far somewhat accustomed to Dutch expressions 
                    
                    I saw &#x27; felt 
                    <!-- Nieuwe pagina -->
                    only what I liked in the book.
                    
                    To render it agreeable to the english taste it would at last become no translation.
                    
                    I took the book to a Dutch literary person who thoroughly knows enlish &#x27; has resided in England 
                    
                    for some years &#x27; she thought as I. </p>
                <lb></lb>
                
                <p>&#x27;&#x27;Hilda Hall&#x27;&#x27;was finished last January 
                    
                    - a tale - it will appear in May. 
                    
                    If you would like to do business with the 
                    
                    &#x27;&#x27;Charing Cross&#x27;&#x27; Society, 
                    
                    or become an agent for 
                    
                    &#x27;&#x27;Hilda Hall&#x27;&#x27; 
                    
                    please write to Mr. Tomkins secretary 
                    
                    5&#x27;riar st Broadway. 
                    
                    Either in english or in French- but Dutch is very little understood in England.
                    
                    I mentioned your firm at the office. I believe a very 
                    <!-- Nieuwe pagina -->
                    great number of English books
                    
                    are read in Holland &#x27; at present I do not think the 
                    
                   &#x27;&#x27;Charing Cross&#x27;&#x27; office
                   
                    has an agent in Holland.</p>
                <lb></lb>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        <p>I am Sir </p>
                        
                        <p>Yours very respectfully</p>
                        
                    </salute>
